<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n25069a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n25" href="#n25069a">N25 (VI.B.15)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n25all.htm#n25069a"> 69(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> drive thorns in / soleprint</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The putting of sharp stones in the foot-tracks of an enemy is believed to maim him, as <mark>a nail is driven into a horse&apos;s footprint</mark> to lame him, the chewing of a piece of wood is thought to soften the heart of a man with whom a bargain is being driven. <small> Edward Clodd, <a name="ECTTT" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ECTTT"><cite title="source">Tom Tit Tot</cite></a> (1898) 61</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c14040i" href="c14all.htm#c14040i">VI.C.14:040(i)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
